### Test 1: Word found in database (hello)
GET {{baseUrl}}/ipa?word=hello

### Test 2: Word with weak/strong forms (and)
GET {{baseUrl}}/ipa?word=and

### Test 3: Word found in database (beautiful)
GET {{baseUrl}}/ipa?word=beautiful

### Test 4: Word NOT in database - should try Wiktionary fallback (cryptocurrency)
GET {{baseUrl}}/ipa?word=cryptocurrency

### Test 5: Word NOT in database - should try Wiktionary fallback (algorithm)
GET {{baseUrl}}/ipa?word=algorithm

### Test 6: Non-existent word - should return 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/ipa?word=asdfghqwerty

### Test 7: Common word (the)
GET {{baseUrl}}/ipa?word=the

### Test 8: Word with different pronunciations (read)
GET {{baseUrl}}/ipa?word=read

### Test 9: Transcribe full text with notFound feedback
POST {{baseUrl}}/transcribe
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Hello world, this is a test with unknownword123 in it.",
  "accent": "american",
  "useWeakForms": true,
  "ignoreStress": false
}

